== Description ==

Epackage refers to two terms:

* It is a DVCS repository that has a laid out according to [[DELPS]] specification.
  In short: some Emacs utility has been wrapped in a Git repository, made publicly available e.g. through http://github.com
  and announced in a specific central "Yellow page".
* It a is the name of reference implementation of the [[DELPS]]. The Emacs extension is called ##epackage.el##.
  With it, you can download, install, remove and manage packages.
  Similar to the manner of [[ELPA]] package manager.

See [[DELPS]] page and its links for more information about how to make epackages and where to get ##epackage.el##.

